{
  "texts": [
    "If a possibility model M = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, π⟩ is such that ⟨S, ⊑⟩ has a minimum element, then for every formula φ ∈ L(Φ, I), either φ M = S or φ M = ∅.",
    "Fact 4.21 (Incoherence).",
    "For any extended possibility model M and formula φ ∈ L(Φ, I), M, ⊥ ⊩ φ.",
    "Example 4.22 (Extended Powerset Possibilization).",
    "Given a world frame F = ⟨W, {R i } i∈I, A⟩ and a world model M = ⟨F, V⟩, the extended powerset possibilizations of F and M, F ℘ Proposition 4.31 will follow from Proposition 5.22.3 and Theorem 5.23.1 in § 5.3."
  ]
}